Q1 Which of the following statements are correct.

(i)      Data is a collection of symbols, raw facts and transactions that have been recorded but not yet processed. It could be quantitative or qualitative

(ii)     Information is data that has been processed in such a way that it becomes meaningful.

(iii)    Information is used for decision making at the strategic, tactical and operational levels.
 

(iv)   Information is vital because it is required by internal users only.

options.label: (i), (ii) and (iv)

Q2 Which of the following are NOT different structural types introduced in ACCA Textbook?

(i)       Entrepreneurial structural type means typical in small owner managed companies.

(ii)      Geographical structural type means activities are grouped according to location

(iii)     Matrix structural type means a combination of the functional and divisional with dual reporting lines.

(iv)     Divisional structural type means departments are based on common specialisation. Best suited to companies operating in a stable environment with few products.

options.label: (i), (ii) and (iv)
